Talon Community Dual License Agreement

Copyright (c) 2026 Talon Contributors

Talon offers a dual-licensing model designed to protect the core technology from unethical commercial exploitation by cloud providers, while ensuring it remains entirely free and open for the vast majority of developers, startups, and enterprises.

You may choose to use this software under ONE of the following two licenses:

========================================================================
OPTION 1: SERVER SIDE PUBLIC LICENSE (SSPL) v1
Best for: Individual developers, academic research, startups, and enterprises integrating Talon into an application, product, or service (as long as you are NOT offering Talon itself to third parties as a managed Database-as-a-Service, Platform-as-a-Service, or similar cloud-hosted infrastructure).

Under the SSPL, you are free to use, modify, and distribute the software. However, if you make the functionality of the software or a modified version available to third parties as a service, you must make the source code of both the software and the entire service stack (including management software, user interfaces, application programming interfaces, automation software, monitoring software, backup software, storage software and hosting software) publicly available under the SSPL.
(The full SSPL text is provided below).

OPTION 2: TALON COMMERCIAL ENTERPRISE LICENSE
Best for: Cloud providers, hyperscalers, or any enterprise that wishes to offer Talon as a managed service (SaaS/DBaaS/PaaS) without open-sourcing their proprietary management and infrastructure code under the SSPL.

To obtain a Commercial Enterprise License, you must contact the Talon maintainers for a bespoke agreement prior to any commercial deployment.
========================================================================

If you have not executed a separate Commercial Enterprise License with the Talon project, you are automatically bound by the terms of the Server Side Public License (SSPL) version 1.

